'''''Star Wars 65: Golrath Never Forgets''''' is the sixty-fifth issue in the [[Star Wars (1977)|''Marvel Star Wars'']] series of comics.

==Plot summary==
[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] is placed on trial for the negligent death of [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Lumiya|Shira Brie]]. A small judges panel, presided over by [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]], [[General/Legends|General]] [[Carlist Rieekan/Legends|Rieekan]] and General [[Duron Veertag]] examine the evidence of the past several days and conclude that Skywalker is innocent of all charges. He is reinstated into the fleet at the rank of [[Commander/Legends|commander]] once again.

Later, a [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] named [[Gemmer Sojan/Legends|Gemmer]] complains about the photoreceptive imagery from a souvenir piece of rock from the old [[Golrath/Legends|Golrath]] base keeping him awake at night. Captain [[Hanc Thorben|Thorben]] has Gemmer turn the piece over to the Rebel leaders who quickly examine it. They discover that the natural mineral deposits found on the volcanic world record light images of their surroundings and project them as holograms once the mineral cools. They know that the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperials]] have recently taken control of Golrath, and are scared that this geological peculiarity might yield the location of their current base at [[Arbra/Legends|Arbra]]. Leia decides to personally lead an expedition to Golrath to eradicate any trace elements that might aid the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] in their search for the fleet.

[[Golrath Station]] is currently presided over by the recently demoted Lieutenant [[Mils Giel]]. He soon learns about the bedrock's astounding properties when two [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] report seeing images of a Rebel training exercise. Giel immediately sends a communiqué to [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] and orders a squad of [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE fighters]] to defend the base should the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]] return.

Two flight groups of [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] and [[BTL Y-wing starfighter/Legends|BTL Y-wing starfighters]] converge on Golrath. They engage with a squadron of Imperial TIE fighters and a vicious battle takes place. Princess Leia maneuvers her Y-wing through the morass of fighters and dives down into the clouds above Golrath. She flies down towards the old base using a [[parabelt]] rocket harness.

Leia sneaks into the factory compound and heads directly towards the reactor core. Her intent is to overload the core causing the base to explode. Giel finds her and opens fire, causing Leia to seek cover behind some packing crates. Giel seals off all of the exits and primes the overload switches himself. As valuable a prize as this base may be to the Empire, the chance of killing the leader of the Rebel Alliance is of even greater value – even at the cost of his own life. Leia manages to distract Giel by activating her rocket harness and finds a way to escape from the reactor room. He chases her outside, but is unable to stop her. She radios [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] in a Y-wing who meets her at a rendezvous point.

Giel is enraged at his failure. Out of spite, he fires off a shot from his blaster at a passing X-wing fighter before boarding his own [[Imperial troop transport]]. Giel evacuates the base just before it explodes. As luck would have it, the ship he fired upon belongs to Luke Skywalker and the small blaster shot causes enough damage to Luke's engines that he is unable to regroup with the fleet. As the rest of the ships enter [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]], Luke is left behind with a fresh squad of TIE fighters bearing down on him.

==Continuity==
The [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] abandoned [[Golrath/Legends|Golrath]] station in [[Star Wars (1977) 50|''Star Wars'' (1977) 50]].

Capt. [[Lumiya|Shira Brie]] was allegedly killed by Luke Skywalker in [[Star Wars (1977) 61|''Star Wars'' (1977) 61]].

Lt. [[Mils Giel]] was demoted in rank in [[Star Wars (1977) 63|''Star Wars'' (1977) 63]].

In this issue, the [[Imperial troop transport]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] is dressed in the uniform of an [[Imperial gunner/Legends|Imperial gunner]]. In the [[Marvel Comics]] stories, it was common to find various non-commissioned personnel dressed in such a fashion, regardless of job function.

